  "overview": {
    "headline": "A focused, fixed-scope assessment of the Skyworks ODS environment.",
    "background": "The ODS serves dual duty as a transactional and analytical layer, creating performance constraints at peak concurrency, limiting governance visibility, and introducing cost inefficiencies. BPC performs deep metadata ingestion, references upstream and downstream systems for lineage, classifies datasets into a Bronze/Silver/Gold medallion architecture, and produces a prioritized, low-risk transition backlog.",
    "outcome": "All findings, lineage maps, classification reports, and the transition backlog are delivered as final outputs owned by Skyworks.",
